ov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:dlc:batch_dlc_jean_ver01:data:sn82014241:00220720457:1900011301:0005/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg#h=305&w=210", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:dlc:batch_dlc_jean_ver01:data:sn82014241:00220720457:1900011301:0005/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=611&w=421"], "index": 18, "language": ["english"], "location": ["fulton county", "fulton", "georgia", "atlanta", "united states"], "mime_type": ["image/jp2", "application/pdf", "text/xml", "image/jpeg"], "number": ["00220720457", "sn82014241", "1"], "numeric_shelf_id": 190001131, "online_format": ["image", "pdf", "online text"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["serial and government publications division", "chronicling america", "atlanta age (atlanta, ga.) 1898-19??"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 78.89876, "shelf_id": "sn82014241, 1900-01-13, Edition 1", "site": ["chroniclingamerica"], "subject": ["atlanta (ga.)", "fulton county (ga.)", "fulton county", "fulton", "georgia", "atlanta", "newspapers", "african american", "united states", "african american newspapers", "african americans"], "timestamp": "2023-08-08T11:12:37.199Z", "title": "Atlanta age (Atlanta, Ga.), January 13, 1900", "type": ["issue"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn82014241/1900-01-13/ed-1/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83016234/1900-02-01/ed-1/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn83016234/1900-02-01/ed-1/"], "batch": ["dlc_jean_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["library of congress, washington, dc"], "date": "1900-02-01", "dates": ["1900-02-01"], "description": ["Atlanta, Ga."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-08-07T20:32:31.197Z", "group": ["ndnp/dlc-2020_now", "library-of-congress-washington-dc-awardee-8"], "hassegments": true, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83016234/1900-02-01/ed-1/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:dlc:batch_dlc_jean_ver01:data:sn83016234:00220720457:1900020101:0001/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg#h=313&w=220", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:dlc:batch_dlc_jean_ver01:data:sn83016234:00220720457:1900020101:0001/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=627&w=440"], "index": 19, "language": ["english"], "location": ["fulton county", "fulton", "georgia", "atlanta", "united states"], "mime_type": ["image/jp2", "application/pdf", "text/xml", "image/jpeg"], "number": ["00220720457", "sn83016234", "1"], "numeric_shelf_id": 190002011, "online_format": ["image", "pdf", "online text"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["serial and government publications division", "chronicling america", "voice of missions (atlanta, ga.) 1893-1900"], "publication_frequency": ["monthly"], "score": 78.89876, "shelf_id": "sn83016234, 1900-02-01, Edition 1", "site": ["chroniclingamerica"], "subject": ["atlanta (ga.)", "fulton county (ga.)", "fulton county", "fulton", "georgia", "atlanta", "newspapers", "african american", "united states", "african methodist episcopal church", "african american newspapers", "african americans"], "timestamp": "2023-08-08T11:12:37.199Z", "title": "Voice of missions (Atlanta, Ga.), February 1, 1900", "type": ["issue"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn83016234/1900-02-01/ed-1/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn89053729/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn89053729", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/16bcefe0-33e9-5307-bea6-d00e31f50997"], "batch": ["gu_henson_ver02"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1912", "description": ["Daily Began with vol. 10, no. 218 (Apr. 13, 1912); ceased with v. 38, no. 292 (Dec. 16, 1939). Published in several chronological editions. Some issues may also carry statements such as \"Florida extra\" and \"Extra for Carolina\"; cannot always be determined whether these issues are part of true separate geographical editions. Some irregularities in enumeration. Stated publication frequency is every afternoon except Sunday, <May 3, 1912>-September 12, 1913. Sunday American appears to have consituted the Sunday issue of this title and to have existed also as a separate publication in editions for various cities. Sunday edition has its own numbering. Archived issues are available in digital format from the Library of Congress Chronicling America online collection. American Sunday monthly magazine may appear as part of Sunday issue, <June 1913->. May have been issued with various newspapers. Unable to determine relationship to: The Georgian's weekly news briefs and its succeeding title: Weekly Georgian (Atlanta, Ga.). May be weekly editions of this title or may simply be titles also published by the Georgian Company. Vol. X, no. 236 (May 3, 1912) (extra) (online surrogate); title from masthead (Georgia Historic Newspapers archive, viewed July 29, 2021). Vol. XIV, no. 31(September 8, 1915) (final) (online surrogate) (Georgia Historic Newspapers archive, viewed July 29, 2021). Atlanta journal (Atlanta, Ga. : 1889) (DLC)sn 82015426 (OCoLC)8807964"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-06-05T18:25:11.942Z", "group": ["newspaper-titles", "ndnp/newspapers", "catalog-split-12", "catalog", "united-states-newspaper-directory", "main-catalog-split-12"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn89053729/", "image_url": [], "index": 20, "language": ["english"], "latlong": [33.748547, -84.391502], "location": ["fulton county", "fulton", "georgia", "atlanta", "united states"], "location_str": "", "lonlat": [-84.391502, 33.748547], "number": ["1", "original", "sumter cnty hist soc mus-arch", "2025-07-01t13:40:45.900000", "3679", "sn89053729", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "microfilm master", "new york state - vf3", "online resource", "20082372", "sn82015426", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn89053729/1914-08-20/ed-10/", "2833-7077", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn89053729/1912-05-03/ed-1/", "2024-05-12t17:32:27.269094", "univ of georgia", "microfilm service copy", "sn89053728"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_titl